title: Egypt Overnight Interbank Rate
description: Egypt Overnight Interbank Rate was at 13.45 percent on Wednesday November 9. Interbank Rate in Egypt averaged 10.92 percent from 2007 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 19.77 percent in July of 2017 and a record low of 8.25 percent in August of 2010. The interbank rate is the rate of interest charged on short-term loans made between banks in the local currency. This page provides - Egypt Interbank Rate- actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: Central Bank Of Egypt
